What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Project Portfolio Market?

Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Project Portfolio Market

Project portfolio market is expected to grow at a CAGR of 6.90% in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Data Bridge Market Research report on project portfolio provides analysis and insights regarding the various factors expected to be prevalent throughout the forecasted period while providing their impacts on the market’s growth.

The rapidly increasing adoption of cloud-based services for the remote monitoring of assignments is one of the key factors fueling the growth of the project portfolio market. In line with this, surge in activities such as automation and digitalization across various industries counting government, healthcare, BFSI, telecom, and engineering and construction has encouraged the need for monitoring and analytical solutions to increase productivity and business efficiency which are also contributing to the growth of the target market. Increasing adoption of cloud deployment services in small and medium scale enterprises (SMSE) and rising penetration of connected devices in emerging economies and growing investments by major market players in research and development have led to inventive solutions such mobile-application based portfolio management solutions. Such factors are broadly supposed to hasten the growth of the project portfolio market over the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Moreover, the growing complexity in projects and the need for timely and proficient management is also providing a boost to the market growth. However, the growing concerns of organizations related to data confidentiality and high software cost may hamper the adoption of project portfolio and will act as major limitations for the growth of project portfolio in the above mentioned forecasted period.

The inflating disposable incomes, gaining 360-degree view into project operations and resource management along with increasing demand for cloud-based PPM solutions are some other key aspects driving the growth of the overall project portfolio market. Likewise, the falling project costs and project failure rate by embracing agile methods will further cater ample new opportunities that will lead to the growth of the project portfolio market in the above mentioned forecasted period. Whereas, the selecting accurate solution that aligns with organization’s business need and blending modern PPM solutions with legacy systems will challenge the market growth in the above mentioned forecast period.

